Alabama Getaway-> Promised Land, Loser-> Little Red Rooster, Big Railroad Blues, Feel Like A Stranger, Dupree's Diamond Blues, The Music Never Stopped-> Don't Ease Me In

*W Etta James & Tower of Power Horns

reviews.review_text: etta this is just for the tell mamma, 5 stars ain't enough

Fish are rising up like birds.. 1st thing I'd like to say is superb sound quality on this.Nothing to special with 1st set but I like how the Feel Like A Stranger is sandwiched in the middle of the set..a spacey one at that. The 2nd  set opening with Touch..Throwing Stones being new they still where looking for proper placement of these songs..The whole show is pretty tight and well played..but of course the highlight of this show is when Etta James comes out to play double encore of Hard To Handle and Tell MaMa..sweet and powerful..so please GIVE IT A WHIRL!!

Billy dancing Thought it was cool when Billy stood up at the beginning of "He's Gone" and started playin' the tambourine and dancing behind Mickey who is playing solo.. Check it out that sweet moment.
